---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE, GAME } from '../consts';

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'BreadcrumbList', itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: SITE.url },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Cheats', item: new URL('/cheats', SITE.url).href },
  ],
};
---
<Base
  title="Moonlight Peaks Cheats & Console Commands"
  description="Moonlight Peaks cheats and console commands: how the cheat console works and the full money, skill, and item command list — published at launch on July 7, 2026."
  path="/cheats"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  crumbs={[{ label: 'Cheats' }]}
  showExport
>
  <article class="page">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Entry · Cheats</p>
      <h1>Moonlight Peaks <em>cheats</em> & console</h1>
      <p class="intro">
        Whether {GAME.title} ships with player-facing cheats is still not confirmed here, even
        post-launch. Here's what to expect and how cheat consoles in cozy life sims usually work.
        Updated {SITE.updated}.
      </p>

      <h2>Is there a cheat console?</h2>
      <p>
        Not yet confirmed which player-facing cheats {GAME.title} includes, if any. Cozy life sims
        in this space commonly include a console you open with a key combo, then type a command
        such as a money grant or a skill boost — but we haven't verified whether Moonlight Peaks
        has one. We'll document the exact key, the verified commands, and any caveats (for example,
        whether cheats disable achievements) once we can confirm them, rather than guessing.
      </p>

      <h2>Not yet confirmed</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>How to open the console</strong> — the exact key combo, PC and Switch where applicable.</li>
        <li><strong>Money commands</strong> — the verified codes to add currency.</li>
        <li><strong>Skills, needs, items</strong> — the full categorized list, with one-tap copy.</li>
        <li><strong>Warnings</strong> — save-stability and achievement notes.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="callout wip">
        We will not invent commands. Everything here is sourced from the live game or the developers
        — if it's not verified, it won't be listed. Check back as we verify more.
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
